label: Cluster ID
definition: Clusters--defined as one health sub-district--were randomly assigned to one of four study arms. 104 clusters cover 48 districts in Eastern and Western Uganda, and were the unit of randomization for intervention assignment.

label: Windows covered
definition: Whether any of the windows were covered with glass, screens, or other material.
codebookDescription:
Are any of the windows covered?

Glass, screening, other material, etc.

label: Cupboard
definition: Whether the household had a cupboard.
codebookValues: 1 - Yes, 0 - No, -7: Don't know, -8: Refused to answer

label: Desktop computer
definition: Whether any member of the household owned or had access to a desktop computer.
notesForOnt: new term, suggested parent = Assets

label: Internet device type
definition: If any member of the household owned or had access to a device that can access the internet, the type of device.
codebookDescription: If yes, what type of device?
codebookValues: 1 – Smartphone, 2 – Tablet, 3 – Laptop computer, 4 – Desktop computer, -7: Don't know
notesForOnt: new term, suggested parent = Socioeconomic factors

label: Health facility distance
definition: Distance to the nearest health facility, in kilometers. Distances less than 1km were recorded as 0km. Distances greater than 100km were recorded as 100km.
codebookDescription: How far is it to the nearest health facility? If less than 1 km, enter 0. If more than 100 km, enter 100

label: Health facility distance categorization
definition: Categorization of the distance (in kilometers) to the nearest health facility.
codebookDescription: Distance to nearest health facility categories

label: District
definition: 48 districts in Eastern and Western Uganda were included, covering a wide range of epidemiological settings with varying levels of malaria transmission and insecticide resistance.

label: Market distance
definition: Distance to the nearest market, in kilometers.
codebookDescription: How far is it to the nearest market place?

label: Enumeration area ID
definition: The primary sampling unit were  enumeration areas identified in the 2014 Ugandan national census. Ten enumeration areas were randomly selected in each of the health sub-districts. Within each sampled enumeration area, 5 households were randomly enrolled, for a total of 50 households sampled per cluster. .
notesForOnt: new term, suggested parent = Household administrative information

label: Eaves
definition: Type of eaves that the dwelling had.

codebookValues: 1 - Yes, 0 - No, -7: Don't know, -8: Refused to answer
